// Core library: the Set collection.
//
// `Set<T>` is an engine-provided persistent set. Its whole surface —
// `empty`, `insert`, `remove`, `contains`, `length`, `union`,
// `intersection`, `difference`, `to_list` — is a set of intrinsics that
// compile to dedicated opcodes; they attach to this module at
// registration (`intrinsics_for_module`), so it carries no source
// declarations of its own.
